1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,840
Hey! The new kid’s getting jumped
by some 11th graders.

2
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:02,560
- What?
- What?

3
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:04,640
What the f*ck are you guys doing?

4
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:10,480
After all that, why don’t you two join my gang?

5
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:17,080
From now on, I’m Ko Neung,
and this guy’s Ko Song.

6
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:20,240
Hey! Ko Song. What was that for?

7
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,680
From now on, can I call you Orange?

8
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:23,560
What?

9
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:25,320
[KO SONG’S DESK]

10
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:26,360
Sit here forever.

11
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,520
I’m saving this spot just for you.

12
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,160
(The rainy season is known for change.)

13
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:58,960
(Because it’s a very unpredictable season.)

14
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:05,800
(Sometimes, we’re happy about it.)

15
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:08,120
Here we go. Your dad came back quickly…

16
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:10,720
(But at the same time,
someone else may not be.)

17
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,360
[YOUR FOOD’S IN THE FRIDGE.
MICROWAVE IT FOR 3 MINUTES, DEAR.]

18
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:39,320
Wow! I’m wiping this bowl clean.
It’s my favorite.

19
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:41,800
My son’s a greedy little monster.

20
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,920
I’m gonna eat it all.

21
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,880
Eat up, Ko.

22
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,720
Ahem. I’m thirsty.

23
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:49,920
What is it, honey?

24
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,240
-Some water.
-Are you choking?

25
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:51,800
I want some water.

26
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:52,440
Ah, here.

27
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,440
Honey.

28
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,160
I’m off, Mom.

29
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,080
Okay.

30
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,280
- Boss Ko.
- Hm?

31
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,240
- Be careful if it rains.
- Yes, ma’am.

32
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:06,320
(But for new high schoolers,)

33
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:11,840
(this is probably the season when every kind
of relationship grows at full speed.)

34
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,120
Why are you smiling, Orange?

35
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:25,720
Let’s go.

36
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,880
I want it fast and furious, Ko Song.

37
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,840
Why don’t you ride your own bike?

38
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,160
Already complaining after a few days?

39
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,400
Careful, I might kick you out of my gang.

40
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,080
Who says I’m in your gang, Orange?

41
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:02,360
I let you call me Orange.
You’re automatically in.

42
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:08,280
So, your parents leave the house
so early every day?

43
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,680
What? How do you know?

44
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,680
I peek through the window every day.

45
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,080
Hm?

46
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,120
You’re gullible.

47
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,760
I notice the car is gone every morning.

48
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:24,240
Some days,
they have urgent matters in Bangkok.

49
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:25,880
Ah.

50
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,480
Here.

51
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,080
No. You eat. You’re the one who likes them.

52
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,960
Next time, you can
come have breakfast at my house.

53
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:50,000
My parents cook every morning.

54
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,160
They can even feed the whole village.

55
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,680
Why do you want to be a thug?

56
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:05,440
Who said I do?

57
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,720
You like acting like a gangster.

58
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,600
I just want to be famous.

59
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,920
Really, I mean it.

60
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:24,760
Whoo!

61
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,960
Why is Ko late today?

62
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:33,720
Which Ko?

63
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,280
There are two Kos.

64
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,160
Yeah, I mean both of them.

65
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:39,880
This is suspicious.

66
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:41,680
It’s like you’re upset.

67
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,680
Upset, my freaking ass!

68
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,280
I’m just teasing, dude.

69
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,280
[FRIDAY, JUNE 9, 2000]
You get worked up easily.

70
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,880
Hello, my friends.

71
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,960
I brought oranges.

72
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,720
Hold it, tiger.

73
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,200
The owner’s standing right here.

74
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:04,520
Wait for the green light first.

75
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,400
Go ahead.

76
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:10,200
Wow, you guys are fast.

77
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,840
Go back to your seats.

78
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,200
Class.

79
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,520
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning, sir.

80
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:28,160
I have good news and bad news for you.

81
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,640
Can we only hear the good news, sir?

82
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:37,560
The good news is that
today’s science class is a free period

83
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,960
because the teacher
has an urgent matter to attend to.

84
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,400
The bad news is that

85
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:47,640
you’ll be working on the group assignment
during that period instead.

86
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,160
You can turn it in once you’re done.

87
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,080
Don’t slack off. Let’s get started!

88
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:52,880
Have you finished it?

89
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:53,920
Yes, I have.

90
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:55,200
Oh, yes!

91
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:02,640
Uh...

92
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:04,720
Nothing, sir.

93
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:11,880
Alright. I’m going to teach the seniors.
I’ll check on you all later.

94
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,560
You’re the best, Ko Song.

95
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:46,320
Let’s go. I’ll buy you ice cream.

96
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,080
Shouldn’t we wait until lunch break?

97
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:52,320
No way. Where’s the fun in that?

98
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,920
Come on. Hurry up.

99
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:57,960
Right now?

100
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,240
Yeah, right now.

101
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,560
No one’s gonna object, Ko Song.

102
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,280
Where are they going?

103
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,520
Probably off to cause trouble.

104
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:08,840
Classic Ko Neung.

105
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,520
Let’s eat some oranges. They’re really good.

106
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,520
Don’t know how to peel one?

107
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,960
Here, let me help you.

108
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,960
Peeling oranges isn’t hard.

109
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,400
You just have to do it properly.

110
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,720
What happens if you don’t?

111
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,280
Ow! I got orange juice in my eye!

112
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,240
Tle, help me! Tle!

113
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,960
Ow! It stings!

114
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,960
Why do you like doing risky things?

115
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,800
What if we get caught?

116
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:48,440
We’re not even hiding.
Auntie Mee’s standing right here watching.

117
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,520
Ko, you troublemaker

118
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:53,040
If I see your dad, I’m telling him.

119
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:53,800
Good, Auntie.

120
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,560
You can charge him for the ice cream too.

121
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,520
Being a smartass, huh?

122
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:57,400
Hey!

123
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:01,360
If you tell my dad,
I’ll tell him not to rent a boat to Uncle Nuay.

124
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:01,800
Fine.

125
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,360
Here, Auntie. Please take this.

126
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,720
Throw it away for me. We’re leaving.

127
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,080
Damn you, Ko.

128
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:11,320
See? I’m famous.

129
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:14,560
As long as I’m here,
there’s nothing to be scared of.

130
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,880
There’s a teacher!

131
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,360
Where?

132
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,960
Just kidding.

133
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:29,000
What’s the rush? Huh?

134
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,400
Hey, wait.

135
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,160
What now?

136
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:37,320
That’s enough. I’m not going anywhere else.

137
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,560
I know. But you’re not being careful enough.

138
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,560
Here.

139
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:47,600
If we go this way,
we’ll pass by Mr. Prateep’s class.

140
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:50,160
Which is exactly what we shouldn’t do.

141
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,160
You saw what he was like
in his office last time.

142
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:57,880
We’ll take this way instead.
It’s a bit farther, but definitely safer.

143
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:02,880
Mr. Kong’s teaching the 12th graders,
but he won’t pay attention to us.

144
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,440
He probably won’t even notice us.

145
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,320
I do this all the time.
We’ll make it through just fine.

146
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:09,760
Pretty awesome, right?

147
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,160
Ahem.

148
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:21,720
[GRADE 10, CLASS 6]
Didn’t expect that from you, Kanin.

149
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,040
Next time, don’t do whatever Krittin does.

150
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:24,800
Come on, sir.

151
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:25,720
Hey.

152
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,920
Oh, you and Tle
were chosen by your classmates

153
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,600
for the grade 10 academic contest.

154
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:33,800
Yes, sir.

155
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,280
I’ve got a wedgie, sir.

156
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,720
Nice pose, Boss Ko.

157
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,640
Hey, you.

158
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,360
Stay right there or I’ll call Mr. Kong.

159
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,320
Mr. Kong, he’s messing with me!

160
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:52,880
Sir!

161
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:40,800
Hey!

162
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,080
Why study so hard?

163
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,240
Scared you won’t win the contest?

164
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:50,800
Huh?

165
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,360
What?

166
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,080
Why study so hard?

167
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,000
Go to bed.

168
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:05,320
Boss Ko, go to sleep. It’s a school night.

169
00:12:05,680 --> 00:12:07,280
Yes, my lady.

170
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:14,520
Go to sleep already.
I hope you win tomorrow.

171
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,080
Good night.

172
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,320
You should sleep too, Orange.

173
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,160
Good night.

174
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,480
Is it hard?

175
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:16,000
No. Once you know the trick,
it’s even easier than peeling an orange.

176
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,400
You’re exaggerating.

177
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,800
You’re all about physical strength.

178
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,320
You can’t solve a Rubik’s Cube, Augar.

179
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,840
Says the guy who can?

180
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:23,680
I can’t.

181
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:24,960
Dumbass.

182
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:28,280
You don’t use either your brain
or your strength, so you can’t talk.

183
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:31,520
Achi, you’re laughing way too hard.

184
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,720
And what the hell is up with our boss today?

185
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:39,080
Maybe number two isn’t here,
so number one feels lonely.

186
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,480
Gosh.

187
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:52,240
Have you ever noticed how
it always rains whenever we don’t want it to?

188
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,480
It rains during lunch break.

189
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:58,320
It rains when we’re going home.
It even rains during PE.

190
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:02,200
But it never rains on the way to school.

191
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:08,720
Do you think the rain
wants to come to school?

192
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:12,040
Damn, all that talking just to say
you don’t wanna come to school.

193
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,160
Ko Song’s back.

194
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,560
Hey, Ko Song.

195
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:21,080
How’d it go? Did you win?

196
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:25,680
We got first place.

197
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,800
Wow! Yeah!

198
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:29,920
That’s my disciple!

199
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,920
I picked the right one.

200
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,200
- Huh?
- Huh?

201
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,480
Then I should be called Ko Neung instead.

202
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,520
Hey!

203
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,800
Augar, August, execute him!

204
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,200
- As you wish, Your Highness.
- As you wish, Your Highness.

205
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:49,160
Get him, get him!

206
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:55,400
♪ Every time that we meet again ♪

207
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:59,560
♪ Something grows a little more each day ♪

208
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:04,840
♪ The closer we are
The more I feel the love I’ve waited for ♪

209
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:07,720
♪ Might not be too far away at all ♪

210
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:11,480
♪ Even when winter fades I’ll still wait on ♪

211
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:15,440
♪ Till the final raindrop falls
Hope is never gone ♪

212
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:19,880
♪ As long as I have you
Holding my hand as we walk on ♪

213
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:26,400
♪ I fear nothing if this season has you ♪

214
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:45,000
♪ When the sky clears after the storm ♪

215
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:49,080
♪ We start our journey together and move on ♪

216
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:53,080
♪ Every story we go through
Turns into a memory ♪

217
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:58,440
♪ That reminds us how far
We have come along ♪

218
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,440
Come eat at my house tomorrow.

219
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:25,720
Bye-bye.

220
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:27,560
See you.

221
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,280
See you.

222
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,800
Here, have some Kaeng Som, dear.

223
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,080
Thank you, ma’am.

224
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:43,560
Of course.

225
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:47,360
Believe me now when I say
we can feed the whole village?

226
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:50,560
This is to celebrate Ko Song
winning the contest.

227
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,800
Did you tell your mom
to call me Ko Song too?

228
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,080
Why?

229
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:03,120
I’m famous. That’s the power I have.

230
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,280
Here.

231
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:11,240
Ko Song, if you have time,
could you tutor my Ko Neung?

232
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:16,080
I keep lecturing him, but he never listens.

233
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:22,120
Boss Ko, your friend’s smart.
You should learn from him.

234
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,800
Come on, Mom.

235
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:28,480
People are good at different things.
You know?

236
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,440
And what exactly is my son good at?

237
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:32,960
Ah!

238
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:37,560
He’s good at going out,
playing around, and sleeping.

239
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,520
It’s called having life experience.

240
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:44,320
Right, Mr. Sixteen-Year-Old
with all that “life experience.”

241
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:48,280
Actually, Orange—oops!

242
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:55,720
I mean, Ko Neung’s helped me a lot.

243
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:58,600
I’ll help him study, ma’am.

244
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,520
That’s awesome, kiddo.

245
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,520
Did you hear that, my lady?

246
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,760
Are we clear?

247
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:05,640
Yes.

248
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:11,280
Ko Song, whenever your parents
aren’t home, you can always come eat here.

249
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,280
No trouble at all.

250
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:14,480
Thank you, ma’am.

251
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,840
No matter which Ko you are,
I love all the Kos.

252
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:21,400
Hey! You have to love me more.

253
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,400
I’ve been with you since I was in your belly.

254
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:26,480
Yes! And the moment you came out,
you became your dad’s favorite.

255
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:27,280
Jeez!

256
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:27,920
Jeez!

257
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:29,360
Eat.

258
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,800
Hurry up. There’s more food coming.

259
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,240
What are you, a kid, Orange?

260
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:39,360
(Call your father “Orange.”)

261
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,880
My father’s not home.

262
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:45,200
Just eat.

263
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,120
Want some omelet?

264
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:47,680
Not right now.

265
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,560
I got here first.

266
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:59,760
Who could beat you? You run crazy fast.

267
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,840
“Want to take a walk
on the beach with me this Sat?”

268
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,400
Hey, August!
Does someone have a crush on you?

269
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:27,560
Augar, shut up.

270
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:28,680
Shut up.

271
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,800
Fine, I’ll stop teasing you. Promise.

272
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:38,440
Swear it.

273
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:39,360
Yeah.

274
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,280
Who’s this?

275
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,680
Now that’s the right question.

276
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:51,240
Who is this?

277
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:53,000
You don’t know?

278
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,240
I saw it at the same time you did.

279
00:19:57,360 --> 00:20:00,520
Maybe someone’s messing with me.

280
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,280
I don’t think so.

281
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:08,080
Damn, I’ve got goosebumps.

282
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:09,960
Don’t tell anyone.

283
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,120
Okay

284
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,560
August is in love?

285
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:15,680
Funny, isn’t it?

286
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,680
But who’s messing with him?

287
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:18,720
Was it you, Ko Neung?

288
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:19,600
Hey, it wasn’t me.

289
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,960
I thought it was you.

290
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,320
No, not me.

291
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:23,360
Maybe...

292
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,520
Nah, that doesn’t add up.

293
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:31,760
Not even close.

294
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,520
So this is real, yeah?

295
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:43,880
Clearly!

296
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,080
Augar, you asshole!

297
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:47,680
Hey, it’s not like that. Hear me out first.

298
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:49,680
I’m not messing with you.

299
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:54,120
Someone really does have a crush on you.
This is real.

300
00:20:56,640 --> 00:21:00,040
Now you’ve gotta figure out who it is.

301
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,320
Seriously?

302
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:12,760
Yep!

303
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:33,920
Achi, why are you still at school?

304
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:38,320
I’m waiting for my mom to pick me up.
You said this is the safest place.

305
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,320
Mm, true.

306
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,760
But I can’t stay and protect you forever.

307
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,880
You’ve gotta learn
to take care of yourself too.

308
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:50,240
I’m trying.

309
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,960
Why are you studying?
Why not come play basketball with me?

310
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,880
I don’t know how to play.

311
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,360
I’ll teach you.

312
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,360
Don’t think so. I’m not ready today.

313
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:24,440
Reading every day is so boring. It’s stressful.

314
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,760
Not really. I want to get good at it.

315
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:32,360
You practice basketball every day until your
ankle hurts, and you never get tired of it.

316
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:37,800
You’re pretty observant.

317
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,800
Everyone has already gone home.
Why are you still practicing?

318
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,880
Maybe I’m like you.
I want to get good at it too.

319
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:06,840
Achi, theories teach you things.
Practice proves they’re true.

320
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:15,840
Let’s go.

321
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:58,400
It’s okay. That was just your first try.

322
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:02,880
Come on.

323
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:31,040
If you divide the number you got by four,
you’ll get the answer you want.

324
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,720
Hey, Orange

325
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,200
Wake up and study with me.

326
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,440
So when the teacher calls on you,
you’ll know the answer.

327
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:46,680
I can barely keep my eyes open, Ko Song.

328
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:50,720
We’re almost done.

329
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,040
Want to keep studying in my room?

330
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:18,040
My back hurts.

331
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,880
Hey, it’s raining.

332
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,720
Come on, let’s go. Hurry.

333
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:33,120
Dammit.

334
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,560
So, what do you think of my room?

335
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:57,320
Pretty cozy, right?

336
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:00,560
Pretty messy.

337
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,800
It’s not messy. I just have a lot of collectibles.

338
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:08,000
Come on, let’s keep working on our report.

339
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,160
Why are you in such a rush?

340
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:11,160
Hey.

341
00:26:11,560 --> 00:26:12,240
Tomorrow’s our day off.

342
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:15,080
And the rain just keeps coming down all day.

343
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,440
Look at this.

344
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:22,440
The view of your room from my window.

345
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,760
I shout at you from here.
Do you seriously not hear me?

346
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:36,880
If your mom walks into your room and
sees us through the window, that’d be weird.

347
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,160
Shit!

348
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,360
Your mom should be gone by now.

349
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:26,520
I guess so.

350
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:43,080
I should head home.

351
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:45,680
My mom’s probably looking for me.

352
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:30,440
Hey, Dad.

353
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,240
Why did you come home so late this time?

354
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:36,280
I’m famous. Everyone at the market
kept stopping me to chat.

355
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,240
Wow, big shot.

356
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,440
Good thing you’re up, Ko. I’m going to bed.

357
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,600
Hold on.

358
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:42,480
What?

359
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:44,400
Didn’t you buy me anything to eat?

360
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:47,320
Oh, please. If you’re hungry,
go buy something at the market.

361
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:48,120
I’m tired.

362
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:52,280
Jeez. Mom’s gone for one day
and look at you.

363
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,480
I’m telling her about this.

364
00:28:56,760 --> 00:28:58,160
Take the money from under my bike seat.

365
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:00,320
And keep your mouth shut.

366
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:02,880
Awesome.

367
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:04,200
Awesome.

368
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:06,880
20 baht is enough, Ko.

369
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,720
Yeah, I’ll leave you 20.

370
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:09,560
Hey, what are you doing here?

371
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,600
Hi. I’m checking out some books.

372
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:13,960
What do you have there?

373
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,240
English.

374
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:19,800
So he came here to check out girls.

375
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:23,480
Hey! It’s Mr. Famous Ko himself.

376
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:24,840
What are you spying on?

377
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,640
Hey, Master Toh!

378
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,920
Got any interesting comic books?

379
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:35,120
Here, you’ve gotta read this one. Hold on.

380
00:30:42,760 --> 00:30:44,960
Hey there, my friend Ko Song.

381
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:48,880
Didn’t expect to see you here.

382
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:53,560
Checking out girls
without telling your friends, huh?

383
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:57,440
She’s a contestant
from the same academic contest.

384
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,600
Ah!

385
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:03,400
So you met her once
and already have a crush?

386
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:04,400
What are you doing here, Orange?

387
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:06,680
I…

388
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:08,960
I came to buy pancake rolls.

389
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,560
They sell pancake rolls in another alley.

390
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:16,640
Well...

391
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:21,960
I already ordered some. I’m just waiting.
I didn’t wanna stand there doing nothing.

392
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,280
Because you’re famous?

393
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:28,240
Of course.

394
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:31,760
You followed me here and got caught
because you’re so famous.

395
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:34,520
I didn’t follow you.

396
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:38,440
Fine, I’ll believe you.

397
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:43,840
Hey, why are you smiling like that?

398
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,160
Huh?

399
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:46,880
Ko Song!

400
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:50,440
Here it is, Ko.

401
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:51,440
Ko!

402
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,000
Hey!

403
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:56,640
Nobody bought anything.

404
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:02,960
Ko!

405
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:05,360
Ko!

406
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:09,960
What is it, dear?

407
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:12,480
Good morning, ma’am.

408
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:12,840
Morning.

409
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:14,400
I came to pick Ko up.

410
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:17,320
Oh, Boss Ko left for school really early today.

411
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:19,480
I thought you two went together.

412
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:21,840
No, ma’am.

413
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,480
Why are you unusually late today, Ko Song?

414
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:42,680
I had something to take care of.

415
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:45,440
Wow, our gang’s really popular these days.

416
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:47,400
Someone’s got a crush on August.

417
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:49,200
And a bunch of girls like Ko Song.

418
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:54,680
Hey, Boss Ko’s pretty popular too.
I just don’t go around bragging about it.

419
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:56,880
Do you think I should reply?

420
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:57,920
Yeah, you should.

421
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,280
Of course, you should.

422
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:03,080
Tell them, “I wanna see you too.”

423
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:06,720
But you don’t even know
who you’re replying to.

424
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:10,240
I’ll just leave it under my desk.

425
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,320
Get ready for class.

426
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:14,080
Take out your books.

427
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,200
Class.

428
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,840
- Good morning, ma’am.
- Good morning, ma’am.

429
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,160
What’s up with you?

430
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,760
Why didn’t you tell me
you were leaving first, Orange?

431
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,000
I waited for you.

432
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:56,840
Are you mad because I made new friends?

433
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,280
That’s ridiculous.

434
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,320
Why would I be mad?

435
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:40,240
[DARUNTHAMMANUKUL SCHOOL]

436
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:43,080
[MR. KANIN SIRITARA]
[MR. TECHIN RUNGCHAROENCHAI]

437
00:34:43,240 --> 00:34:44,840
Ko Song has accomplished a lot.

438
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,040
Do you think he’ll stop being friends with us?

439
00:34:47,720 --> 00:34:49,320
No. Ko Song’s not like that.

440
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:53,560
I’ll be right back.

441
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:01,800
I’ve got to shoot for the school’s promo.

442
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,320
You guys can head home. Don’t wait for me.

443
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:06,240
Holy shit, I’m jealous.

444
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:07,560
You’re so cool.

445
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,520
You’re famous now, Ko Song.

446
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:11,560
See you later.

447
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:18,320
Let’s split up. I’ve gotta practice basketball.

448
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:19,960
Achi, you coming?

449
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:20,560
Mm.

450
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:22,000
What about me?

451
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,240
Go deal with your love letter.

452
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:27,440
What the heck?

453
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:30,720
They seriously just left me.

454
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:34,680
What’s wrong?

455
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:38,440
I’m drowsy.

456
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:40,880
Yawn!

457
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,240
Yaaawn!

458
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:23,640
Aren’t you practicing?

459
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:27,200
Just waiting for them to finish warming up.

460
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,200
I’m keeping you company for now.
So you won’t be lonely.

461
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:32,760
How’s your ankle?

462
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:36,160
Fully healed.

463
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:38,960
My bones are stronger than
Wolverine’s, kiddo.

464
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:44,480
You talk big, just like Ko Neung.

465
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,480
Ko Neung’s not the same anymore.

466
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:56,040
You and Ko Neung are really close, right?

467
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:57,880
August told me.

468
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:02,920
Mm. The three of us grew up together.

469
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:05,320
Our parents are friends.

470
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,120
So you guys have been close for a long time.

471
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:12,760
I’m not so sure anymore.

472
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:15,040
Ko’s always with Ko Song now.

473
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:25,880
Then I’ll be your close friend, Augar.
So you won’t feel lonely.

474
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:27,600
You sure?

475
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:28,880
Yeah, I’m sure.

476
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:38,240
I’m heading home now. My ride’s here.

477
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:40,040
Bye-bye.

478
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:40,840
Bye.

479
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:43,520
Hold on, sir.

480
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:44,640
I’m still in here.

481
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:16,120
What are you doing?

482
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,280
What? Nothing.

483
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:20,640
I’m...

484
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:23,360
I’m not waiting for you.

485
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:24,880
I didn’t say anything.

486
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:34,320
About this morning... sorry.

487
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:42,080
Sorry for what exactly?

488
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:45,720
About this morning.

489
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:48,720
This morning?

490
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:50,720
What about it?

491
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:57,360
I didn’t wait for you to go to school together.

492
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:03,360
I’m not mad at you.

493
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:07,800
But?

494
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:14,960
Next time, if something’s on your mind,
can you just talk to me honestly?

495
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:16,720
Talk about what?

496
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:18,400
There’s nothing to talk about.

497
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:20,440
Then what about yesterday,
when you followed me?

498
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,000
Followed you?

499
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:24,600
I told you, I didn’t.

500
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,240
I really went there for books.

501
00:40:30,080 --> 00:40:33,080
I wasn’t there to
see Gift like you think, Orange.

502
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:38,680
Okay.

503
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:40,120
I’m sorry.

504
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:45,600
And what exactly are you apologizing for?

505
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:50,760
For everything.

506
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:54,520
For assuming and for following you there.

507
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,280
Thank you.

508
00:41:06,640 --> 00:41:07,320
For what?

509
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:11,880
Thank you for apologizing.

510
00:41:16,240 --> 00:41:18,840
Actually, I already stopped being mad
at you back at school.

511
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:23,160
Mom!

512
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:24,960
Ow!

513
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:26,080
Ow!

514
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,720
My stomach hurts. I’m hungry.

515
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:31,440
I’m starving.

516
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,040
Mom!

517
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:32,840
Mom!

518
00:41:33,040 --> 00:41:33,480
Mom!

519
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:35,400
Mom!

520
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:48,920
What’s this?

521
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:05,800
You said I couldn’t hear you
when you shouted.

522
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:07,920
Is this better?

523
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:11,720
Yeah, much.

524
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:13,360
It’s like getting free phone calls.

525
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:16,720
Use this to tell me
if you wanna go to school together.

526
00:43:19,720 --> 00:43:20,600
Well...

527
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:23,640
You can use it to wake me up too.

528
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:36,480
(And I think I’m right.)

529
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:39,400
(The rainy season is
the most unpredictable season of all.)

530
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:51,400
(It doesn’t just bring the rain...)

531
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:57,200
Ankle injury treatment?

532
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:03,400
(...it also brings
rain-soaked memories of youth.)

533
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:18,680
“I don’t know who you are,
but I’d like to meet you.”

534
00:44:30,560 --> 00:44:35,560
(And for some people, the rainy season
might even bring their first love.)

535
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:48,720
I hope you win tomorrow.

536
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:50,920
Good night.

537
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:05,280
Good night, Ko Neung.

538
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:14,360
(The kind of first love they never forget.)

539
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:40,680
Do you think this is the last rain of the season?

540
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:42,680
Why?

541
00:45:43,680 --> 00:45:45,640
I can’t tell you. I’m afraid it’ll come true.

542
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:46,120
Orange.

543
00:45:47,240 --> 00:45:48,320
The storm’s finally over.

544
00:45:48,720 --> 00:45:49,800
Anyone wanna go out to sea with me?

545
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:51,480
Why’d you agree to go this time?

546
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:53,320
Because...

547
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:07,200
It’s your first time.
